rival.definition: A competitor (person, team, company, etc.) with the same goal as another, or striving to attain the same thing. Defeating a rival may be a primary or necessary goal of a competitor.

river.definition: A large and often winding stream which drains a land mass, carrying water down from higher areas to a lower point, oftentimes ending in another body of water, such as an ocean or in an inland sea.

rivet.definition: A cylindrical mechanical fastener that attaches multiple parts together by fitting through a hole and deforming the head(s) at either end.

roach.definition: Certain members of the fish family Cyprinidae, including:

roads.definition: A way used for travelling between places, originally one wide enough to allow foot passengers and horses to travel, now (US) usually one surfaced with asphalt or concrete and designed to accommodate many vehicles travelling in both directions. roast.definition: A cut of meat suited to roasting

robin.definition: Any of various passerine birds (about 100 species) of the families Muscicapidae, Turdidae and Petroicidae (formerly Eopsaltriidae), typically with a red breast.

rocks.definition: An enormous mythical bird in Eastern legend.

rogue.definition: A scoundrel, rascal or unprincipled, deceitful, and unreliable person.

roles.definition: A character or part played by a performer or actor.

rolls.definition: The act or result of rolling, or state of being rolled.

roman.definition: One of the main three types used for the Latin alphabet (the others being italics and blackletter), in which the ascenders are mostly straight.

roost.definition: The place where a bird sleeps (usually its nest or a branch).

roots.definition: The part of a plant, generally underground, that anchors and supports the plant body, absorbs and stores water and nutrients, and in some plants is able to perform vegetative reproduction.

ropes.definition: Thick strings, yarn, monofilaments, metal wires, or strands of other cordage that are twisted together to form a stronger line.

roses.definition: A shrub of the genus Rosa, with red, pink, white or yellow flowers.

rosin.definition: A solid form of resin, obtained from liquid resin by vaporizing its volatile components.

rotor.definition: A rotating part of a mechanical device, for example in an electric motor, generator, alternator or pump.

rouge.definition: Red or pink makeup to add colour to the cheeks; blusher.

rough.definition: The unmowed part of a golf course.

round.definition: So as to form a circle or trace a circular path, or approximation thereof.

route.definition: A course or way which is traveled or passed.

rover.definition: (usually in the plural) A randomly selected target.

royal.definition: A royal person; a member of a royal family.

rugby.definition: (usually uncountable) A form of football in which players can hold or kick an ovoid ball. ruins.definition: (sometimes in the plural) The remains of a destroyed or dilapidated construction, such as a house or castle.

ruled.definition: To regulate, be in charge of, make decisions for, reign over.

ruler.definition: A (usually rigid), flat, rectangular measuring or drawing device with graduations in units of measurement; a straightedge with markings.

rural.definition: A person from the countryside; a rustic.

safer.definition: Not in danger; out of harm's reach.

saint.definition: A person whom a church or another religious group has officially recognised as especially holy or godly; one eminent for piety and virtue.

salad.definition: A food made primarily of a mixture of raw or cold ingredients, typically vegetables, usually served with a dressing such as vinegar or mayonnaise.

salon.definition: A large room, especially one used to receive and entertain guests.

salsa.definition: A spicy tomato sauce, often including onions and hot peppers.

salts.definition: A common substance, chemically consisting mainly of sodium chloride (NaCl), used extensively as a condiment and preservative.

salve.definition: An ointment, cream, or balm with soothing, healing, or calming effects.

salvo.definition: An exception; a reservation; an excuse.

sands.definition: Rock that is ground more finely than gravel, but is not as fine as silt (more formally, see grain sizes chart), forming beaches and deserts and also used in construction.

satin.definition: A cloth woven from silk, nylon or polyester with a glossy surface and a dull back. (The same weaving technique applied to cotton produces cloth termed sateen).

sauce.definition: A liquid (often thickened) condiment or accompaniment to food.

saucy.definition: Similar to sauce; having the consistency or texture of sauce.

sauna.definition: A room or a house designed for heat sessions.

saves.definition: In various sports, a block that prevents an opponent from scoring.

savor.definition: The specific taste or smell of something.

scald.definition: A burn, or injury to the skin or flesh, by hot liquid or steam.

scale.definition: A ladder; a series of steps; a means of ascending.

scalp.definition: The top of the head; the skull.

scarf.definition: A long, often knitted, garment worn around the neck.

scary.definition: Causing or able to cause fright.

scene.definition: The location of an event that attracts attention.

scoff.definition: Derision; ridicule; a derisive or mocking expression of scorn, contempt, or reproach.

scoop.definition: Any cup- or bowl-shaped tool, usually with a handle, used to lift and move loose or soft solid material.

scope.definition: The breadth, depth or reach of a subject; a domain.

score.definition: The total number of goals, points, runs, etc. earned by a participant in a game.

scout.definition: A person sent out to gain and bring in tidings; especially, one employed in war to gain information about the enemy and ground.

scowl.definition: The wrinkling of the brows or face in frowning; the expression of displeasure, sullenness, or discontent in the countenance; an angry frown.

scrap.definition: A (small) piece; a fragment; a detached, incomplete portion.

screw.definition: A device that has a helical function.

scrub.definition: One who labors hard and lives meanly; a mean fellow.

scrum.definition: A tightly-packed and disorderly crowd of people.

scuba.definition: (underwater diving) An apparatus carried by a diver, which includes a tank holding compressed, filtered air and a regulator which delivers the air to the diver at ambient pressure which can be used underwater.

sedan.definition: An enclosed windowed chair suitable for a single occupant, carried by at least two porters, in equal numbers in front and behind, using wooden rails that passed through metal brackets on the sides of the chair.

seeds.definition: A fertilized and ripened ovule, containing an embryonic plant.

segue.definition: An instance of segueing, a transition.

seize.definition: To deliberately take hold of; to grab or capture.

sense.definition: Any of the manners by which living beings perceive the physical world: for humans sight, smell, hearing, touch, taste.

sepia.definition: A dark brown pigment made from the secretions of the cuttlefish.

serif.definition: A short line added to the end of a stroke in traditional typefaces, such as Times New Roman.

serum.definition: The clear yellowish liquid obtained upon separating whole blood into its solid and liquid components after it has been allowed to clot.

serve.definition: An act of putting the ball or shuttlecock in play in various games.

seven.definition: The digit/figure 7 or an occurrence thereof.

shaft.definition: The entire body of a long weapon, such as an arrow.

shake.definition: The act of shaking or being shaken; tremulous or back-and-forth motion.

shalt.definition: (modal, auxiliary verb, defective) Used before a verb to indicate the simple future tense in the first person singular or plural.

shank.definition: The part of the leg between the knee and the ankle.

shear.definition: A cutting tool similar to scissors, but often larger.

sheep.definition: A woolly ruminant of the genus Ovis.

sheet.definition: A thin bed cloth used as a covering for a mattress or as a layer over the sleeper.

shell.definition: A hard external covering of an animal.

shill.definition: A person paid to endorse a product favourably, while pretending to be impartial.

shoal.definition: A sandbank or sandbar creating a shallow.

slash.definition: A slashing action or motion, particularly:

sower.definition: One who sows; one who scatters seeds.

speck.definition: A tiny spot, especially of dirt etc.

speed.definition: The state of moving quickly or the capacity for rapid motion; rapidity.

spend.definition: Amount of money spent (during a period); expenditure.

spiff.definition: Attractiveness or charm in dress, appearance, or manner.

wispy.definition: Consisting of or resembling a wisp; like a slender, flexible strand or bundle.

witch.definition: A person who practices witchcraft; a woman or man who practices witchcraft.

wives.definition: A married woman, especially in relation to her spouse.

woken.definition: (often followed by up) To stop sleeping.

wolds.definition: An unforested or deforested plain, a grassland, a moor.

wonky.definition: A subgenre of electronic music employing unstable rhythms, complex time signatures, and mid-range synths.

woods.definition: The substance making up the central part of the trunk and branches of a tree. Used as a material for construction, to manufacture various items, etc. or as fuel.

woody.definition: An early station wagon or estate car in which the rear portion of the car's bodywork is made of wood, often associated with Southern California surfing culture.

wooed.definition: To endeavor to gain someone's support.

wooer.definition: A person who admires another; a person who seeks to win someone's favor or affection.

wools.definition: The hair of the sheep, llama and some other ruminants.

words.definition: The smallest unit of language that has a particular meaning and can be expressed by itself; the smallest discrete, meaningful unit of language. (contrast morpheme.)

wordy.definition: Using an excessive number of words.

world.definition: (with "the") Human collective existence; existence in general.

worms.definition: A generally tubular invertebrate of the annelid phylum; an earthworm.

wormy.definition: Of or like a worm or worms; shaped like a worm or worms.

would.definition: Something that would happen, or would be the case, under different circumstances; a potentiality.

wound.definition: An injury, such as a cut, stab, or tear, to a (usually external) part of the body.

woven.definition: To form something by passing lengths or strands of material over and under one another.

wrack.definition: Vengeance; revenge; persecution; punishment; consequence; trouble.

wraps.definition: A sharp blow with something hard.

wreak.definition: To cause something harmful; to afflict; to inflict; to harm or injury; to let out something harmful; .

wreck.definition: Something or someone that has been ruined.

wrest.definition: The act of wresting; a wrench or twist; distortion.

wring.definition: A powerful squeezing or twisting action.

wrist.definition: The complex joint between forearm bones, carpus, and metacarpals where the hand is attached to the arm; the carpus in a narrow sense.

write.definition: The act or style of writing.

writs.definition: A written order, issued by a court, ordering someone to do (or stop doing) something.

wrong.definition: Something that is immoral or not good.

wrote.definition: To form letters, words or symbols on a surface in order to communicate.

wrung.definition: To squeeze or twist (something) tightly so that liquid is forced out. See also wring out.

yacht.definition: A slick and light ship for making pleasure trips or racing on water, having sails but often motor-powered. At times used as a residence offshore on a dock.

yanks.definition: A sudden, vigorous pull (sometimes defined as mass times jerk, or rate of change of force).

yappy.definition: Of a dog, yapping in an annoying manner.

yards.definition: A small, usually uncultivated area adjoining or (now especially) within the precincts of a house or other building.

yarns.definition: A twisted strand of fiber used for knitting or weaving.

yawls.definition: A small ship's boat, usually rowed by four or six oars.

yawns.definition: The action of yawning; opening the mouth widely and taking a long, rather deep breath, often because one is tired or bored.

yearn.definition: To long, have a strong desire (for something).

years.definition: A solar year, the time it takes the Earth to complete one revolution of the Sun (between 365.24 and 365.26 days depending on the point of reference).

yeast.definition: An often humid, yellowish froth produced by fermenting malt worts, and used to brew beer, leaven bread, and also used in certain medicines.

yield.definition: To pay, give in payment; repay, recompense; reward; requite.

yokes.definition: Frame around the neck, and related senses.

yolks.definition: The yellow, spherical part of an egg that is surrounded by the white albumen, and serves as nutriment for the growing young.

yours.definition: That which belongs to you (singular); the possessive second-person singular pronoun used without a following noun.

youth.definition: The quality or state of being young.

yowls.definition: A prolonged, loud cry, like the sound of an animal; a wail; a howl.

yucky.definition: Of something highly offensive; causing aversion or disgust.

zebra.definition: Any of three species of genus Equus: E. grevyi, E. quagga, or E. zebra, all with black and white stripes and native to Africa.

zesty.definition: Having a strong, tangy, or piquant taste.

zincs.definition: A chemical element (symbol Zn) with an atomic number of 30, a slightly brittle blue-silvery metal.

zoned.definition: To divide into or assign sections or areas.

zones.definition: Each of the five regions of the earth's surface into which it was divided by climatic differences, namely the torrid zone (between the tropics), two temperate zones (between the tropics and the polar circles), and two frigid zones (within the polar circles).
